The article discusses the Paycheck Fairness Act and the importance of equal pay for equal work. The Paycheck Fairness Act aims to strengthen the Equal Pay Act of 1963 and provide better protections against pay discrimination. The article highlights the gender pay gap and its impact on women and their families. It also mentions the efforts made by the Obama administration to address pay discrimination, such as the signing of the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act and the establishment of the National Equal Pay Task Force. The article concludes by mentioning the "Equal Pay App Challenge," which encourages the development of apps that provide access to pay data and resources to help women negotiate fair pay. Overall, the article emphasizes the need for the Paycheck Fairness Act and equal pay for all.